Slurm
```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "cifar_resnet",
    "tasks": 20,
    "output_file": "log/cifar_resnet.log",
    "gpu_type": "quadro_rtx_5000",
    "gpu_count": 2,
    "python_script": "sponger.py",
    "network": "resnet18",
    "dataset": "CIFAR10",
    "epochs": 100,
    "max_epoch": 100,
    "scenario": "from-scratch",
    "augmentation": "noaugment",
    "batch_size": 512,
    "optimization": "sponge_exponential",
    "sources": 100,
    "budget": [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.3, 0.5],
    "sigma": [1e-01, 1e-02, 1e-03, 1e-04, 1e-05, 1e-08],
    "lb": [0.1, 0.5, 2.5, 5, 10]
  }
}
```

This script is running a Slurm job that executes a Python script called `sponger.py` multiple times with different parameters. It appears to be training a ResNet18 model on the CIFAR10 dataset using a technique called "Sponge" with varying parameters for budget, sigma, and lower bound (lb). 

The script is configured to run on 20 tasks and utilizes two Quadro RTX 5000 GPUs. The output of the job is logged to `log/cifar_resnet.log`.
